  </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">This is pretty simple. A few explainations...<br>
<br>
Ric Olie&#146;s ability to reduce attrition has made him a valuable asset in the few games I&#146;ve played with this deck so far. My strategy to deal with probing is this: since the errata, what the enemy will often do is deploy to a system, probe it, and move away all in the same turn. Hence, they will just drop one little ship to save force. All I do is play Rebel Barrier, and then smash them nicely on my turn. Obviously, Haven will be played on Sullust, which is some icing on the cake. I have five weapons just so I can use  interrupts that play off weapons to insure my superiority in the air. I can put Luke in Red 5 if he isn&#146;t absolutely needed on the ground, and it&#146;s a good destiny either way. Finally, Porkins and Red 6 are in there for the destiny of 6, plus I like to make the point that just because you&#146;re fat, it doesn&#146;t mean that you can&#146;t be a good pilot (example of myself...) Well, I think that&#146;s it. Thank you for your time.       </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech SW: CCG <BR> Play With Power <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
